{"word":"ἀγγέλλω","slug":"ἀγγέλλω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀγγέλλω</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to bear a message</i>, <el>τινί</el> <i>to</i> a person, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> et <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to make proclamation</i> that, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> rei, <i>to announce, proclaim, report</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, attic<p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> <i>to bring news of</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; <el>περί τινος</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> <i>to announce oneself</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be reported of</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>τὰ ἠγγελμένα</el> <i>the reports</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}